title: The Legend of Harley Davidson (gnv64)
description: The Legend of Harley Davidson Edite by Steven Myatt Dennis Publishing | April 2011 | ISBN: 190637273X | 220 pages | PDF | 39 mb No one can argue against Harley-Davidson's position as the most famous motorcycle brand in the world. This collectors' MagBook celebrates the Harley throughout the ages and contains exhilarating images, special features covering the legendary Sturgis party, military Harleys, 105 essential Harley facts and much more. The king of all bikes, the Harley-Davidson is synonymous with rock stars, danger and of course, Hells Angels. Highlighting why the Harley has earned its place in the motoring hall of fame, this MagBook created by industry expert Steven Myatt revels in the iconic status of the Harley as it reveals the legendary history of the brand. Exploring the Harley's humble beginnings to its present status as the world's most desirable bike, this MagBook contains detailed line-ups of the greatest Harley engines, looks at the female pioneers of motorcycling, delves into the exhilarating heritage of H-D racing and remembers the Harley's most famous rider, Evel Knieval This all-encompassing MagBook is a great guide for any Harley owner or fan, both young and old.
